[1] Lethal bark canker - Germany (Hesse): emerging pathogen
Date: Thu 14 Jul 2011
Source: Wiesbadener Kurier [in German, trans. & summ. Mod.DHA,
edited]
http://www.wiesbadener-kurier.de/region/rheingau/geisenheim/10948391.htm


Bark canker affects apple trees in drought conditions
-----------------------------------------------------
The Hessian Minister of Agriculture Puttrich reported on the results
of a 3 year project on bark canker of apple at the Research Institute
Geisenheim (RIG).

The disease appears mainly in hot and dry years like 2003, says Peter
Braun, RIG. A normally harmless bark endophyte virtually explodes,
with drought being the main factor. The fungus is called _Diplodia
mutila_. This parasite infects weakened trees affected by drought
stress and can lead to their death.

Since there are no approved fungicides to combat the fungus, it is
recommended to improve plant vigour by watering and fertilisers. Dead
wood should be removed. For new plantings, location and varieties
should be carefully selected. Braun agrees with other scientists that
due to climate change bark canker will be a long term problem.

[Additional news story (in German):
http://www.proplanta.de/Agrar-Nachrichten/Pflanze/Puttrich-Kampf-gegen-das-Apfelbaum-Sterben_article1310606435.html]

[Byline: Thorsten Stoetzer]

