[2] Marssonina blotch - India (Himachal Pradesh)
Date: Sun 17 Jul 2011
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Early-leaf-fall-destroys-apple-crop-in-Kullu/articleshow/9253812.cms


Early leaf fall destroys apple crop
-----------------------------------
The unseasonal leaf and fruit fall are giving sleepless nights to
apple growers in Kullu. Suffering with the Marssonina disease, apple
trees are increasingly losing their leaves and fruits. Farmers said
frequent hailstorms destroyed apples everywhere in the state [Himachal
Pradesh]. Now, this dangerous disease is back to destroy the remaining
crop. It spreads quickly from one tree to another and to other
orchards.

A fruit grower said, "The view is same everywhere. At first leaves
turned yellow and then they started falling down fast. And now apples
too are falling rapidly." Another farmer said, "Insecticides and
pesticides have no effect on the disease. This diseases is affecting
the growth of the plant. It has stopped new bud and leaf formation and
is also affecting the quality of fruit."

According to scientists, Marssonina becomes more active during
monsoon and a predetermined spray schedule is the only way to control
this deadly disease.

[Byline: Suresh Sharma]

